summary: Strategic review identified two completeness approaches: (1) Semantic FMP path using `semantic_weak_completeness` is sorry-free and in main build - this is the publishable path; (2) Representation path has 27 sorries and broken imports excluding it from build. Recommend keeping Semantic FMP as primary, archiving broken WeakCompleteness.lean and InfinitaryStrongCompleteness.lean files.

artifacts.summary: Strategic comparison of Semantic FMP vs Representation approaches with archival recommendations
